==English==
===Etymology===
The word is first known in English from the 15th century. Although the etymology is uncertain, the most likely origin is thought to be from the Middle Dutch ''colf'', meaning "club". Note that the idea that "golf" is an [[acronym]] from "gentlemen only, ladies forbidden" is false - this is a [[folk etymology]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒlf|-ɒlf]]

===Noun===
'''golf''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

#A [[ball game]] played by individuals competing against one another in which the object is to hit a ball into each of a series of (usually 18 or nine) holes in the minimum number of [[stroke]]s.
#The letter ''G'' in the [[ICAO spelling alphabet]].

